#1 Resected recurrent rectal adenocarcinoma
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Dawn Divers's Service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Doug Martin, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
As outlined by Mr. Haynes's primary oncologist at Maplewood Manor Personal Home, Dr. Alderson, adjuvant chemotherapy is generally recommended.  Mr. Haynes is planning on returning to New York, receiving care under his local medical oncologist, therefore, I will not make follow-up appointments for him to return in the outpatient setting.  We would recommend adjuvant chemotherapy.  A KRAS status has been ordered and is currently pending.  When available, the results will be notified to Dr. Alderson and then passed on to his local medical oncologist in New York.  I have indicated to Mr. Haynes that if any problems or concerns arise at any time, I am more than happy to help facilitate care.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

